<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,225,1643]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Description: Typical member of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[659,768,225,250]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Verdanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[659,768,225,250]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Verdanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as in 
<figureCitation box="[849,920,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,255,1767,1791]" captionTargetBox="[169,1417,410,1705]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,390,1733]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. (A) Landscape in the Tuscan-Emilian Apennines near Passo delle Radici, type locality of Verdanus tyrannus sp. nov.; (B) Southern slope of M. Corchia (Alpi Apuane), type locality of Verdanus saurosus sp. nov.; (C) Southern slopes of Alpe di Succiso, type locality of Verdanus rosaurus rosaurus ssp. nov.; (D) M. Cavalbianco, type locality of Verdanus rosaurus rex ssp. nov.; (E) Verdanus rosaurus rosaurus ssp. nov., male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190801/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Fig. 
<number box="[904,920,225,251]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
E). Very similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1147,1323,225,250]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Verdanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abdominalis">
<emphasis box="[1147,1323,225,250]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">V. abdominalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in shape, proportions, size, colouration and markings of body, legs and fore wings. Upper side pale green, apical cells of fore wings caudally brownish bordered. Fore wings about as long as abdomen (only sub-brachypterous specimens were collected). Generally the pattern of blackish colouration on frontoclypeus, ventral part of thorax and abdomen and on legs is highly variable.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,225,1643]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Male genitalia: Pygofer lobes terminating at the posteroventral apex in a posteriorly directed short spur (as in Fig. 
<number box="[279,294,457,483]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="4.0">4</number>
A) and with a bundle of macrosetae on the dorsal edge. Genital plates (as in 
<figureCitation box="[1205,1274,457,483]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,257,1492,1516]" captionTargetBox="[259,1330,217,1443]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[188,1399,178,1467]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Left genital plate, ventral view, (A) Verdanus rosaurus rosaurus ssp. nov., male (paratype: Italy, Emilia Romagna, M. Navert); (B) Verdanus bensoni (China) (paratype of Deltocephalus obenbergeri Dlabola: Bohemia, det. Dlabola, 1945, MNHN (EH) 3502); (C) Verdanus limbatellus (Zetterstedt) (Russia, bassin of Manya river, Great Ural, Liapin &amp; Flerov leg., 21. - 23. VII. 1927). - Right genital plate, dorsal view, (D) Verdanus tyrannus sp. nov., male (paratype: Italy, Emilia Romagna, M. Cervarola)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190807/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Fig. 
<number box="[1260,1274,457,483]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
A) long, ratio length of median lobe/width of genital plate base normally 
<number box="[842,882,496,522]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="0.9">0.9</number>
-1.0; macrosetae arranged along lateral borders; dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[261,329,534,560]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,257,1492,1516]" captionTargetBox="[259,1330,217,1443]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[188,1399,178,1467]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Left genital plate, ventral view, (A) Verdanus rosaurus rosaurus ssp. nov., male (paratype: Italy, Emilia Romagna, M. Navert); (B) Verdanus bensoni (China) (paratype of Deltocephalus obenbergeri Dlabola: Bohemia, det. Dlabola, 1945, MNHN (EH) 3502); (C) Verdanus limbatellus (Zetterstedt) (Russia, bassin of Manya river, Great Ural, Liapin &amp; Flerov leg., 21. - 23. VII. 1927). - Right genital plate, dorsal view, (D) Verdanus tyrannus sp. nov., male (paratype: Italy, Emilia Romagna, M. Cervarola)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190807/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Fig. 
<number box="[315,329,534,560]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
D) with a short black spur near the medioapical border of the lateral lobe. Styles (Figs. 
<number box="[1344,1360,534,560]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="4.0">4</number>
D, 
<number box="[1394,1409,534,560]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="4.0">4</number>
E) with slender laterally curved apical process. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[858,944,573,599]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="15.[151,257,1828,1852]" captionTargetBox="[181,1417,212,1738]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,197,1803]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 5. Aedeagus. Verdanus tyrannus sp. nov., male (paratype: Italy, Emilia Romagna, Passo delle Radici), (A) ventral view; (B) ventrolateral view; (C) lateral view; (D) caudal view. - Verdanus saurosus sp. nov., male (paratype: Italy, Toscana, M. Corchia), (E) ventral view; (F) ventrolateral view; (G) lateral view; (H) caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190803/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Figs. 
<number box="[930,944,573,599]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
A-D) stocky. Basal apodeme with long caudolaterally protruding arms, their apex somewhat bent in ventral direction. Shaft wide and, in lateral view, thin and slightly S-shaped curved, apically with a pair of leaf-like broad acute, distally narrowed and caudally directed appendages, their surface oriented perpendicularly to the sagittal plane (their maximal extension visible in ventral view), and subapically a pair of small triangular, laterally directed processes (
<figureCitation box="[1266,1347,728,754]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="15.[151,257,1828,1852]" captionTargetBox="[181,1417,212,1738]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,197,1803]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 5. Aedeagus. Verdanus tyrannus sp. nov., male (paratype: Italy, Emilia Romagna, Passo delle Radici), (A) ventral view; (B) ventrolateral view; (C) lateral view; (D) caudal view. - Verdanus saurosus sp. nov., male (paratype: Italy, Toscana, M. Corchia), (E) ventral view; (F) ventrolateral view; (G) lateral view; (H) caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190803/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Figs. 
<number box="[1333,1347,728,754]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
A, 
<number box="[1384,1399,728,754]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="5.0">5</number>
B); phallotreme terminal.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,225,1643]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Female genitalia: Praegenital sternite (as in Fig. 
<number box="[784,799,805,831]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="4.0">4</number>
F) posteriorly with median bifurcate protuberance, to some degree variable in shape. Ovipositor base (as in 
<figureCitation box="[818,918,844,870]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="20.[151,255,1707,1731]" captionTargetBox="[202,1370,233,1644]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,178,1682]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 10. Base of ovipositor, ventral view, (A) Verdanus rosaurus rosaurus ssp. nov., female, (paratype: Italy, Emilia Romagna, M. Navert); (C) Verdanus bensoni (China) (Krkonoše [Czech Republic], 10. VI. 1946, Dlabola, MNHN 3507); (F) Verdanus limbatellus (Zetterstedt) (Russia, bassin of Manya river, Great Ural, Liapin &amp; Flerov leg., 21. - 23. VII. 1927). - Base of ovipositor, rostral view, (B) Verdanus rosaurus rosaurus ssp. nov., female, (paratype: Italy, Emilia Romagna, M. Navert); (D) Verdanus bensoni (China) (Krkonoše [Czech Republic], 10. VI. 1946, Dlabola, MNHN 3507); (E) Verdanus limbatellus (Zetterstedt) (Russia, bassin of Manya river, Great Ural, Liapin &amp; Flerov leg., 21. - 23. VII. 1927)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190808/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Figs. 
<number box="[887,918,844,870]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
A, 
<number box="[955,986,844,870]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="10.0">10</number>
B) with medioventral part somewhat protruding anteriorly.
</paragraph>
