is known only from M. Cimone (M. Cervarola) and Passo delle Radici (Tuscan-Emilian Apennines) (
<figureCitation box="[653,725,1462,1488]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,259,1215,1239]" captionTargetBox="[174,1410,187,1191]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,152,1211]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Distribution map of new taxa. ♦ = Verdanus tyrannus sp. nov.; ˑ = Verdanus saurosus sp. nov.; ● = Verdanus rosaurus rosaurus ssp. nov.; ․ = Verdanus rosaurus rex ssp. nov .." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190800/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Fig. 
<number box="[708,725,1462,1488]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1.0">1</number>
